{"title":"The New Trek Verve+ 2 and Verve 3 Gen 5 Hybrids Look Clean w/ Internal Cockpit Routing","link":"https://bikerumor.com/new-trek-verve-2-verve-3-gen-5-hybrids/","date":1721834722000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-hero-1536x1025.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" alt=\"(Photos / Trek Bicycles)\" /></p>\n<p>Just recently, Wisconsin’s <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/\" target=\"_blank\">Trek Bicycles</a> released its all-new <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/hybrid-bikes/electric-hybrid-bikes/verve/verve-2-lowstep-gen-3/p/41518/?colorCode=bluedark\" target=\"_blank\">Verve+ 2</a> comfort hybrid eBikes. The new Verve+ comes with a powerful Bosch motor and a Bluetooth-capable Smart System, ready for city streets and easy commutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ready-for-the-commute-e1721665527286.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"740\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ready-for-the-commute-e1721665527286.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike ready for the commute\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ready-for-the-commute-e1721665527286.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ready-for-the-commute-e1721665527286-297x172.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ready-for-the-commute-e1721665527286-120x69.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ready-for-the-commute-e1721665527286-768x444.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Trek Black (Photos / Trek Bicycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like all new Verve+ models, the Verve+ 2 puts comfort first. With frame geometry, grips, and saddles designed to keep you fresh, the Verve+ 2 is ready for your longest rides.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-Dark-Aquatic-e1721665551607.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"740\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-Dark-Aquatic-e1721665551607.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike Dark Aquatic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-Dark-Aquatic-e1721665551607.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-Dark-Aquatic-e1721665551607-297x172.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-Dark-Aquatic-e1721665551607-120x69.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-Dark-Aquatic-e1721665551607-768x444.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Dark Aquatic</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The all-new Bosch Smart System lets you keep your bike current with over-the-air updates and allows you to pair your e-bike to your phone for even more customization.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike ergo cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-ergo-cockpit-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-control-panel.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-control-panel.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike control panel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-control-panel.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-control-panel-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-control-panel-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-control-panel-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some of the new features of the Verve+ 2 eBikes,</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>New! Bosch Smart System</strong><br />The new Bosch Smart System allows you to connect your ebike to the Ebike Flow App and customize your ride assist, see range maps, and so much more.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>New! Integrated Bosch PowerTube battery</strong><br />A 400Wh Bosch Compact PowerTube battery offers 50 miles of range and is integrated into your downtube for added safety and protection from the elements. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>New! PowerMore Range Extender</strong><br />Go even further with the option to add an additional 250Wh external battery.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Upright not uptight</strong><br />The ultimate comfort bikes feature upright, easygoing geometry, ergonomic grips, and a plush saddle for miles and miles of smiles. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Hill-Shrinking Boost</strong><br />An Active Line Plus Drive Unit provides up to 50Nm of torque that’s perfect for crushing hills and the start-and-stop of city riding.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-plugged-in.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-plugged-in.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike plugged in\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-plugged-in.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-plugged-in-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-plugged-in-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-plugged-in-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-lights.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-lights.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike lights\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-lights.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-lights-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-lights-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-lights-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Verve+ 2 Lowstep Gen 3</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail $2899</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Colors: Trek Black, Dark Aquatic, and Plasma Grey Pearl</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sizes: S, M, and L</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-bosch-motor.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-bosch-motor.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike bosch motor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-bosch-motor.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-bosch-motor-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-bosch-motor-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-bosch-motor-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Verve+ 2 Lowstep is a powerful electric hybrid bike that will help you get out and ride more. Your daily cruises, commutes, and workouts will all get a boost from the Bosch Active Line Plus motor with smart system technology that lets you map rides, track activity, and more. Plus, this e-bike is equipped with parts that put your comfort and safety first, like wide, stable tires, an easy-to-mount lowstep frame, ergonomic touchpoints, and front and rear lights</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Verve+ 2 Features</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Sleek and compact battery</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Plush touchpoints</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fully integrated digital experience</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bosch ActiveLine Plus</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-essa-8-speed-drivetrain-cues-short-reach-new-hubs/\" target=\"_blank\">Shimano CUES</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shoimano LinkGlide</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stepthrough geo</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easy to read display</li>\n\n\n\n<li>MIK Rack</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Battery extender</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hydraulic disc brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sleek Cable Integration</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Verve+ 2 Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-geo-e1721400289733.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"795\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-geo-e1721400289733.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve Low Step hybrid bikes geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-geo-e1721400289733.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-geo-e1721400289733-297x184.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-geo-e1721400289733-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-geo-e1721400289733-768x477.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-geo.jpg\"><img width=\"370\" height=\"573\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-geo.jpg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve+ 2 Comfort eBike geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-geo.jpg 370w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-geo-194x300.jpg 194w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-2-Comfort-eBike-geo-77x120.jpg 77w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>New Verve Hybrids without Motors Too!</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-Verve-3-full-bike-e1721400368780.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"802\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-Verve-3-full-bike-e1721400368780.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve Low Step hybrid bikes Verve 3 full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-Verve-3-full-bike-e1721400368780.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-Verve-3-full-bike-e1721400368780-297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-Verve-3-full-bike-e1721400368780-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-Verve-3-full-bike-e1721400368780-768x481.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-verve-2-full-bike-e1721400384540.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"793\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-verve-2-full-bike-e1721400384540.jpeg\" alt=\"Trek Bicycles Verve Low Step hybrid bikes verve 2 full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-verve-2-full-bike-e1721400384540.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-verve-2-full-bike-e1721400384540-297x184.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-verve-2-full-bike-e1721400384540-120x74.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Trek-Bicycles-Verve-Low-Step-hybrid-bikes-verve-2-full-bike-e1721400384540-768x476.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to the Verve+ 2 ebikes, Trek is also introducing a new Verve Gen 5 hybrid bike with a similar design language. Equipped with Shimano CUES drivetrains, the bikes move to internal cable routing that’s routed through the headset. Fortunately, there is a new adjustable stem included so there shouldn’t be much need for swapping stems. The Gen 5 model is only available as a Verve 3 and in lowstep, otherwise, the existing Verve 2 and 3 models continue. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both of these bikes are available for direct-to-home delivery, or in-store pickup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/\" target=\"_blank\">TrekBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-trek-verve-2-verve-3-gen-5-hybrids/\">The New Trek Verve+ 2 and Verve 3 Gen 5 Hybrids Look Clean w/ Internal Cockpit Routing</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"43f74b4711630794593eafa93329d54d784101abeb02ece9924ab967749fa0ce","category":"Cycling"}